verses.text_plain: Then came all the tribes of Israel to David unto Hebron, and spake, saying, Behold, we are thy bone and thy flesh.
verses.verse_html: 1Then came all the tribes of Israel to David unto Hebron, and spake, saying, Behold, we are thy bone and thy flesh.

verses.text_plain: Also in time past, when Saul was king over us, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the Lord said to thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be a captain over Israel.
verses.verse_html: 2Also in time past, when Saul was king over us, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the Lord said to thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be a captain over Israel.

tokens.text: over us, thou wast he that leddest out
and thou shalt be a captain

verses.text_plain: So all the elders of Israel came to the king to Hebron; and king David made a league with them in Hebron before the Lord: and they anointed David king over Israel.
verses.verse_html: 3So all the elders of Israel came to the king to Hebron; and king David made a league with them in Hebron before the Lord: and they anointed David king over Israel.

verses.text_plain: David was thirty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned forty years.
verses.verse_html: 4David was thirty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned forty years.

verses.text_plain: In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months: and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty and three years over all Israel and Judah.
verses.verse_html: 5In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months: and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty and three years over all Israel and Judah.

verses.text_plain: And the king and his men went to Jerusalem unto the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land: which spake unto David, saying, Except thou take away the blind and the lame, thou shalt not come in hither: thinking, David cannot come in hither.
verses.verse_html:
6And the king and his men went to Jerusalem unto the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land: which spake unto David, saying, Except thou take away the blind and the lame, thou shalt not come in hither: thinking, David cannot come in hither.
 thinking: or, saying David shall not, etc

footnotes.body_text: thinking: or, saying David shall not, etc
footnotes.body_html: thinking: or, saying David shall not, etc

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless David took the strong hold of Zion: the same is the city of David.
verses.verse_html: 7Nevertheless David took the strong hold of Zion: the same is the city of David.

verses.text_plain: And David said on that day, Whosoever getteth up to the gutter, and smiteth the Jebusites, and the lame and the blind, that are hated of Davids soul, he shall be chief and captain. Wherefore they said, The blind and the lame shall not come into the house.
verses.verse_html:
8And David said on that day, Whosoever getteth up to the gutter, and smiteth the Jebusites, and the lame and the blind, that are hated of Davids soul, he shall be chief and captain. Wherefore they said, The blind and the lame shall not come into the house.
 Wherefore: or, Because they had said, even the blind and the lame, He shall not

tokens.text: he shall be chief and captain

footnotes.body_text: Wherefore: or, Because they had said, even the blind and the lame, He shall not
footnotes.body_html: Wherefore: or, Because they had said, even the blind and the lame, He shall not

verses.text_plain: So David dwelt in the fort, and called it the city of David. And David built round about from Millo and inward.
verses.verse_html: 9So David dwelt in the fort, and called it the city of David. And David built round about from Millo and inward.

verses.text_plain: And David went on, and grew great, and the Lord God of hosts was with him.
verses.verse_html:
10And David went on, and grew great, and the Lord God of hosts was with him.
 went: Heb. went, going and growing

footnotes.body_text: went: Heb. went, going and growing
footnotes.body_html: went: Heb. went, going and growing

verses.text_plain: And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, and carpenters, and masons: and they built David an house.
verses.verse_html:
11And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, and carpenters, and masons: and they built David an house.
 masons: Heb. hewers of the stone of the wall

footnotes.body_text: masons: Heb. hewers of the stone of the wall
footnotes.body_html: masons: Heb. hewers of the stone of the wall

verses.text_plain: And David perceived that the Lord had established him king over Israel, and that he had exalted his kingdom for his people Israels sake.
verses.verse_html: 12And David perceived that the Lord had established him king over Israel, and that he had exalted his kingdom for his people Israels sake.

verses.text_plain: And David took him more concubines and wives out of Jerusalem, after he was come from Hebron: and there were yet sons and daughters born to David.
verses.verse_html: 13And David took him more concubines and wives out of Jerusalem, after he was come from Hebron: and there were yet sons and daughters born to David.

verses.text_plain: And these be the names of those that were born unto him in Jerusalem; Shammua, and Shobab, and Nathan, and Solomon,
verses.verse_html: 14And these be the names of those that were born unto him in Jerusalem; Shammua, and Shobab, and Nathan, and Solomon,

verses.text_plain: Ibhar also, and Elishua, and Nepheg, and Japhia,
verses.verse_html: 15Ibhar also, and Elishua, and Nepheg, and Japhia,

verses.text_plain: And Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphalet.
verses.verse_html: 16And Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphalet.

verses.text_plain: But when the Philistines heard that they had anointed David king over Israel, all the Philistines came up to seek David; and David heard of it, and went down to the hold.
verses.verse_html: 17But when the Philistines heard that they had anointed David king over Israel, all the Philistines came up to seek David; and David heard of it, and went down to the hold.

verses.text_plain: The Philistines also came and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.
verses.verse_html: 18The Philistines also came and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.

verses.text_plain: And David enquired of the Lord, saying, Shall I go up to the Philistines? wilt thou deliver them into mine hand? And the Lord said unto David, Go up: for I will doubtless deliver the Philistines into thine hand.
verses.verse_html: 19And David enquired of the Lord, saying, Shall I go up to the Philistines? wilt thou deliver them into mine hand? And the Lord said unto David, Go up: for I will doubtless deliver the Philistines into thine hand.

verses.text_plain: And David came to Baalperazim, and David smote them there, and said, The Lord hath broken forth upon mine enemies before me, as the breach of waters. Therefore he called the name of that place Baalperazim.
verses.verse_html:
20And David came to Baalperazim, and David smote them there, and said, The Lord hath broken forth upon mine enemies before me, as the breach of waters. Therefore he called the name of that place Baalperazim.
 Baalperazim: that is, the plain of breaches

footnotes.body_text: Baalperazim: that is, the plain of breaches
footnotes.body_html: Baalperazim: that is, the plain of breaches

verses.text_plain: And there they left their images, and David and his men burned them.
verses.verse_html:
21And there they left their images, and David and his men burned them.
 burned: or, took them away

footnotes.body_html: burned: or, took them away

verses.text_plain: And the Philistines came up yet again, and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.
verses.verse_html: 22And the Philistines came up yet again, and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.

verses.text_plain: And when David enquired of the Lord, he said, Thou shalt not go up; but fetch a compass behind them, and come upon them over against the mulberry trees.
verses.verse_html: 23And when David enquired of the Lord, he said, Thou shalt not go up; but fetch a compass behind them, and come upon them over against the mulberry trees.

verses.text_plain: And let it be, when thou hearest the sound of a going in the tops of the mulberry trees, that then thou shalt bestir thyself: for then shall the Lord go out before thee, to smite the host of the Philistines.
verses.verse_html: 24And let it be, when thou hearest the sound of a going in the tops of the mulberry trees, that then thou shalt bestir thyself: for then shall the Lord go out before thee, to smite the host of the Philistines.

tokens.text: And let it be, when thou hearest
thyself: for then shall the Lord

verses.text_plain: And David did so, as the Lord had commanded him; and smote the Philistines from Geba until thou come to Gazer.
verses.verse_html:
25And David did so, as the Lord had commanded him; and smote the Philistines from Geba until thou come to Gazer.
 Geba: also called, Gibeon

footnotes.body_html: Geba: also called, Gibeon
